The paper deals with wireless communication scenarios and interference, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of scheduling algorithms to reduce interference is a common technique in the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the analysis of convergence limits involves game theory and optimization, which are studied in the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
